  "text": "In these enzymatic reactions, phenol is a substrate for tyrosinase, benzoic acid is the inhibitor and MBTH is the color indicator. According to previous works, benzoic acid is a reversible inhibitor (and it can be proved in this study by analyzing the kinetic investigation between tyrosinase, phenol and benzoic acid, see Section 3.6). Based on the theory, the reversible inhibitor is not only bound to the enzyme but also to the enzyme-substrate complex, the active center is usually deformed and its function is thus impaired [CITATION_1] . When this happen, the amount of enzyme-substrate complex will be decreased, due to the inhibition effect of benzoic acid on normal function of tyrosinase. Therefore, the quantities of benzoic acid can be measured based on the decreased amount of enzyme-substrate complex.",
